<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>BLST 221.  The Atlantic Slave Trade: Violence, Exploitation, Resistance.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Thematic social, cultural and economic history tracing rise and fall of Atlantic slave trade from African supply systems to New world consumption 1550-1880 with focus on slave experiences. Course Information: Same as <a href="/search/?P=HIST%20221" title="HIST 221" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'HIST 221');">HIST 221</a>. Previously listed as AAST 221. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=ENGL%20161" title="ENGL 161" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'ENGL 161');">ENGL 161</a>. Class Schedule Information: To be properly registered, students must enroll in one Discussion/Recitation and one Lecture.<i>  Past course, and  World Cultures course</i>.<br/>
</p>
</div><div class="courseblock">
